{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"52e06b07-6709-4e27-b6ad-df637416d593","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Update base images\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Also update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions with `dotnet outdated` or manually in the `.csproj`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"88f17490-48c9-4a15-a245-0dd5b847a421","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":289,"requestId":"D829:44010:60C76C1:6A078C1:69F162A1"},"id":"1bb1480b-e1df-4935-a5da-f0f068b446e9","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:45:12.686Z","parentId":"b474ad69-6071-4eb6-97dd-4e3ba4cf48fc"}
